en


I pushed the doors to the War Room and the large doors swung open.

LineNo: 15572907,

Narrator: The military helicopter gracefully...
en


The military helicopter gracefully landed on the helipad.

LineNo: 15573009,

Narrator: I could see the pillars of smoke fr...
en


I could see the pillars of smoke from the air during the flight.

LineNo: 15573111,

Narrator: As the engine stopped, my ears were...
en


As the engine stopped, my ears were still ringing from the loud noise.

LineNo: 15573213,

Narrator: I fixed the collars of my military...
en


I fixed the collars of my military uniform. I felt comfortable in it. This whole trip reminded me of the good old days at Camp Domus.

LineNo: 15573593,

Narrator: A soldier opened the door to lead m...
en


A soldier opened the door to lead me to the lined up soldiers where General Azaro and many cameras were waiting for me.

LineNo: 15573695,

Taddeus Azaro: ATTENTION!
en


"ATTENTION!"

LineNo: 15573797,

Narrator: All of the soldiers simultaneously...
en


All of the soldiers simultaneously turned and saluted me. The sound from their boots managed to cut through the now slowing down propeller of the helicopter.

LineNo: 15573899,

Taddeus Azaro: I hope you had a good flight, Your...
en


"I hope you had a good flight, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 15574001,

Taddeus Azaro: Thank you for accepting my request...
en


"Thank you for accepting my request, sire. Welcome to FOB Bull Charge."

LineNo: 15574103,

Player_Romus: It is great to be here. I wanted t...
en


"It is great to be here. I wanted to see the frontline with my own eyes."

LineNo: 15574205,

Player_Romus: Skip the pleasantries, General Aza...
en


"Skip the pleasantries, General Azaro. We have much to discuss."

LineNo: 15574307,

Taddeus Azaro: We will momentarily, Your Majesty.
en


"We will momentarily, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 15574409,

Player_Romus: I would much rather be at the Port...
en


"I would much rather be at the Porte Drazon right now. This better be worth my time, General Azaro."

LineNo: 15574511,

Taddeus Azaro: I am glad to hear that, Your Majes...
en


"I am glad to hear that, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 15574613,

Taddeus Azaro: Duchess Azaro will be arriving sho...
en


"Duchess Azaro will be arriving shortly after the protocol and dinner. But for now..."

LineNo: 15574715,

Player_Romus: I sure hope that you did not put y...
en


"I sure hope that you did not put your King in danger by making me come here."

LineNo: 15574817,

Taddeus Azaro: It will be, Your Majesty.
en


"It will be, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 15574919,

Taddeus Azaro: We have taken every precaution, Yo...
en


"We have taken every precaution, Your Majesty. Do not worry."

LineNo: 15575021,

Taddeus Azaro: This way, sir. You must be hungry...
en


"This way, sir. You must be hungry after your ride. We have already prepared your quarters."

LineNo: 15575123,

Narrator: He was right. The pride of the sold...
en


He was right. The pride of the soldiers could be read from their faces.

LineNo: 15575225,

Taddeus Azaro: GLOVURIUS AXA RIZIA!
en


"GLOVURIUS AXA RIZIA!"

LineNo: 15575327,

Narrator: Soldiers joined in and chanted the...
en


Soldiers joined in and chanted the words in unison.

LineNo: 15575429,

Player_Romus: I will dine together with the sold...
en


"I will dine together with the soldiers in the barracks."

LineNo: 15575531,

Player_Romus: Invite this soldier to dine with u...
en


"Invite this soldier to dine with us."

LineNo: 15575633,

Narrator: He gestured towards a tent. Inside,...
en


He gestured towards a tent. Inside, there was a lavish table with an outrageous amount of food, high quality and reserved only for nobility.

LineNo: 15575735,

Narrator: We then proceeded to inspect the so...
en


We then proceeded to inspect the soldiers. I shook hands and saluted until I lost count.

LineNo: 15575837,

Narrator: After saluting, I shook hands with...
en


After saluting, I shook hands with him. I leaned forward to his ear.

LineNo: 15575963,

Narrator: He turned around and saluted the so...
en


He turned around and saluted the soldiers.

LineNo: 15576065,

Narrator: I was not sure if I imagined it but...
en


I was not sure if I imagined it but I heard a soldier gulp. He was merely a boy, barely twenty, skin-and-bones.

LineNo: 15576183,

Player_Romus: I guess this is acceptable. Very w...
en


"I guess this is acceptable. Very well. Let's get on with it."

LineNo: 15576285,

Narrator: We sat down at the table. General A...
en


We sat down at the table. General Azaro gave a brief rundown of the base operations.

LineNo: 15576387,

Narrator: I tried to stomach the terrible foo...
en


I tried to stomach the terrible food. It was perhaps the worst meal of my life but I persevered.

LineNo: 15576489,

Narrator: The soldiers were in awe of what wa...
en


The soldiers were in awe of what was happening. They were having dinner right next to their King!

LineNo: 15576591,

Narrator: Rest of the dinner was rather uneve...
en


Rest of the dinner was rather uneventful. I talked about my time in the military, getting a few laughs from the funny stories I told.

LineNo: 15576971,

Narrator: Rest of the dinner was rather uneve...
en


Rest of the dinner was rather uneventful.

LineNo: 15577073,

Narrator: The soldiers was in awe of what was...
en


The soldiers was in awe of what was happening. He was having dinner right next to their King!

LineNo: 15577175,

Narrator: He was almost tearing up as he prob...
en


He was almost tearing up as he probably never had food of this quality in his life before.

LineNo: 15577277,

Narrator: After the meal, a soldier came by t...
en


After the meal, a soldier came by to let us know that Duchess Azaro has arrived. We moved to another tent.

LineNo: 15577379,

Taddeus Azaro: Please look around you. I can feel...
en


"Please look around you. I can feel the excitement in the air. They see their own King come by their side."

LineNo: 15577481,

Lucita Azaro: Your Majesty. General Azaro.
en


"Your Majesty. General Azaro."

LineNo: 15577599,

Player_Romus: Now that you are here, we can begi...
en


"Now that you are here, we can begin."

LineNo: 15577701,

Player_Romus: It was about time. I thought I was...
en


"It was about time. I thought I was going to die from boredom. Start."

LineNo: 15577803,

Player_Romus: Proceed.
en


"Proceed."

LineNo: 15577905,

Taddeus Azaro: As you wish, sir.
en


"As you wish, sir."

LineNo: 15578199,

Narrator: Cameras went off with blinding flas...
en


Cameras went off with blinding flashes.

LineNo: 15578301,

Narrator: My kingdom was on fire.
en


My kingdom was on fire.

LineNo: 15578403,

Narrator: The military helicopter landed on t...
en


The military helicopter landed on the helipad. As we were lowering, a few medical helicopters took off while another landed.

LineNo: 15578505,

Narrator: A soldier opened the door and salut...
en


A soldier opened the door and saluted immediately. His eyes were blank, looking but not actually seeing. These were the eyes of someone who has seen hell.

LineNo: 15578607,

Narrator: General Azaro was looking at a tabl...
en


General Azaro was looking at a table along with other high ranking officers, arguing loudly.

LineNo: 15578709,

Narrator: After the protocols, General Azaro...
en


After the protocols, General Azaro approached.

LineNo: 15578811,

Narrator: We stopped in front of a soldier, a...
en


We stopped in front of a soldier, at least 2 meter tall man with many scars in his face. He looked proud and boastful, towering over everyone else.

LineNo: 15578913,

Taddeus Azaro: This is Major Tigris. Hero of Fort...
en


"This is Major Tigris. Hero of Fort Ales. He single-handedly eliminated 32 enemy combatants. A record."

LineNo: 15579015,

Taddeus Azaro: One of the best men I have ever se...
en


"One of the best men I have ever seen in my days in the army."

LineNo: 15579117,

Player_Romus_Italic: I gestured him to kiss my ring.
en


I gestured him to kiss my ring.

LineNo: 15579123,

Player_Romus_Italic: I gestured him to kiss my ring.
Menu Text en


Gesture him to kiss your ring.

en


I held my hand on his head and said a prayer.

LineNo: 15579231,

Player_Romus_Italic: I held my hand on his head and said...
Menu Text en


Hold your hand on his head and say a prayer.

LineNo: 15579333,

Player_Romus: On your feet soldier. You bow befo...
en


"On your feet soldier. You bow before no one. Thank you for your service."

LineNo: 15579435,

Narrator: The giant kneeled before me obedien...
en


The giant kneeled before me obediently.

LineNo: 15579561,

Narrator: This honor was granted to very few...
en


This honor was granted to very few people in the military. He kissed the ring in great disbelief and then got up on his feet.

LineNo: 15579663,

Narrator: He was taken aback. He looked at Ge...
en


He was taken aback. He looked at General Azaro and upon his confirmation with a nod, he got up and saluted me.

LineNo: 15579765,

Narrator: He repeated the prayer then got up...
en


He repeated the prayer then got up on his feet.

LineNo: 15579867,

Player_Romus: I expect no less from our army. Ev...
en


"I expect no less from our army. Everyone should strive to be like him."

LineNo: 15579969,

Narrator: He got up on his feet and saluted.
en


He got up on his feet and saluted.

LineNo: 15580071,

Narrator: A scream cut through. A soldier on...
en


A scream cut through. A soldier on a stretcher was crying out for his mother as he was moved into the helicopter. He was covered in bloody bandages.

LineNo: 15580173,

Narrator: General Azaro was unfazed by the sc...
en


General Azaro was unfazed by the scream, looking down at a table along with a few high ranking officers. He turned to my approach when a soldier whisphered in his ear.

Taddeus Azaro: My liege. Thank you for accepting...
en


"My liege. Thank you for accepting my request. Welcome to FOB Iron Gate."

Taddeus Azaro: I hope you had a good flight, Your...
en


"I hope you had a good flight, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 15580479,

en


After saluting, I shook hands with him. I leaned forward to his ear.

en


"I sure hope that you did not put your King in danger by making me come here."

Taddeus Azaro: We have taken every precaution, Yo...
en


"We have taken every precaution, Your Majesty. Do not worry."

LineNo: 15580809,

Player_Romus: I wanted to see the frontline with...
en


"I wanted to see the frontline with my own eyes. Or whatever you can call this mess."

Player_Romus: Skip the pleasantries, General Aza...
en


"Skip the pleasantries, General Azaro. We have much to discuss."

Taddeus Azaro: As you wish, Your Majesty.
en


"As you wish, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 15581115,

Taddeus Azaro: Yes, sire...
en


"Yes, sire..."

Player_Romus: Not even a proper welcoming party...
en


"Not even a proper welcoming party for your King?"

LineNo: 15581319,

Taddeus Azaro: I am sorry, Your Majesty. We were...
en


"I am sorry, Your Majesty. We were in the middle of a strategic discussion."

LineNo: 15581421,

en


"Duchess Azaro will be arriving shortly. But for now..."

LineNo: 15581523,

Taddeus Azaro: Please look around you. I can feel...
en


"Please look around you. I can feel the excitement in the air. They see their own King come by their side."

LineNo: 15581625,

Narrator: Most of the soldiers looked so tire...
en


Most of the soldiers looked so tired that they did not even recognize their King was here.

LineNo: 15581727,

Taddeus Azaro: GLOVURIUS AXA RIZIA!
en


"GLOVURIUS AXA RIZIA!"

Narrator: He turned around and saluted the so...
en


He turned around and saluted the soldiers.

Narrator: A few meek sounds rose from the sol...
en


A few meek sounds rose from the soldiers. Most of them continued with their duties, carrying sand bags and dirt.

Narrator: General Azaro stopped the two soldi...
en


General Azaro stopped the two soldiers who were hurriedly carrying a wounded man on a stretcher. The man was so tall that he did not fit. With those wounds, it was certain.

LineNo: 15582135,

Narrator: General Azaro held his hand and sai...
en


General Azaro held his hand and said a prayer. The wounded man let out a final sigh. Stretcher moved along, slower than before this time.

LineNo: 15582237,

Taddeus Azaro: I remember when he first joined my...
en


"I remember when he first joined my battalion. A good lad. He kept showing everyone photos of his daughter..."

LineNo: 15582363,

Taddeus Azaro: As you say, Your Majesty.
en


"As you say, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 15582465,

Player_Romus: Don't blame yourself. This is not...
en


"Don't blame yourself. This is not your fault. It is mine."

LineNo: 15582567,

Player_Romus: This is entirely your fault. If on...
en


"This is entirely your fault. If only these soldiers had a better general leading them."

LineNo: 15582669,

Player_Romus: My condolences. I am sure he was a...
en


"My condolences. I am sure he was an excellent soldier."

LineNo: 15582771,

Taddeus Azaro: God damn it! That was Major Tigris...
en


"God damn it! That was Major Tigris! One of the best men I have ever seen in my days in the army."

LineNo: 15582873,

Player_Romus: We will take his revenge, General...
en


"We will take his revenge, General Azaro. I promise."

LineNo: 15582975,

Taddeus Azaro: Such words. Forgive me, Your Majes...
en


"Such words. Forgive me, Your Majesty but I can not let you speak ill of yourself. My honor can not allow it."

LineNo: 15583077,

Taddeus Azaro: He was, Your Majesty. He was...
en


"He was, Your Majesty. He was..."

LineNo: 15583179,

Taddeus Azaro: I told you that the left flank is...
en


"I told you that the left flank is no-go! We must first de-"

LineNo: 15583281,

Taddeus Azaro: No matter what, Your Majesty, your...
en


"No matter what, Your Majesty, your presence here is already helping with our situation."

LineNo: 15583383,

Taddeus Azaro: Look around at these men. They fig...
en


"Look around at these men. They fight for their country to their final breath."

LineNo: 15583485,

Narrator: He was right. They looked at me wit...
en


He was right. They looked at me with hope in their eyes. Despite everything.

LineNo: 15583611,

Player_Romus: Sons and daughters of Rizia. Do no...
en


"Sons and daughters of Rizia. Do not falter! We will be victorious! No matter what!"

LineNo: 15583713,

Player_Romus: Times may be tough. But know this,...
en


"Times may be tough. But know this, your sacrifices for our country will never be in vain."

LineNo: 15583815,

Taddeus Azaro: Thank you for your encouraging wor...
en


"Thank you for your encouraging words, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 15583917,

Player_Romus: Fear not. Fight for your King. Fig...
en


"Fear not. Fight for your King. Fight for your country!"

LineNo: 15584019,

Player_Romus: Under one God, we shall return to...
en


"Under one God, we shall return to his bosom one way or another. I would rather it be with pride and honor!"

LineNo: 15584121,

Narrator: Tired soldiers got up on their feet...
en


Tired soldiers got up on their feet. Saluted and started chanting with their weary voices.

LineNo: 15584223,

Narrator: Weary, but loud and clear.
en


Weary, but loud and clear.

A soldier came by to let us know that Duchess Azaro has arrived.

"Right this way, sire."

We moved to the briefing room.

They turned to me and saluted.

"Good evening, Your Majesty."

"Your Majesty. General Azaro."

Lucita got up and gestured at the other military staff present in the room to leave.

Everyone was quiet as they left, leaving me with my thoughts, all alone, in the grand room.

The disgraced general started rolling his wheelchair out.
